# Switch to Gemini 2.5 Flash

The user wants to transition the HawaSentinel autonomous agent from using Groq (Llama 3) to Google's Gemini 2.5 Flash model.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The implementation will switch the primary LLM from Groq to Gemini. This requires a valid Gemini API Key. The existing Groq integration will be replaced in the UI.

## Proposed Changes

### [HawaSentinelDemo]

#### [MODIFY] [agent.py](file:///home/waleedqamar/Documents/hackaton/HawaSentinelDemo/agent.py)
- Rename `groq_api_key` to `gemini_api_key` in `HawaSentinelAgent`.
- Update `_call_llm` to use `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/openai/chat/completions`.
- Set model to `gemini-2.5-flash`.
- Update error handling and docstrings to reflect Gemini usage.

#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///home/waleedqamar/Documents/hackaton/HawaSentinelDemo/app.py)
- Change sidebar input from "Groq API Key" to "Gemini API Key".
- Update environment variable check to `GEMINI_API_KEY`.
- Update UI labels (e.g., "Live Mode (Gemini)").
- Update agent initialization to pass the Gemini key.

#### [MODIFY] [tools.py](file:///home/waleedqamar/Documents/hackaton/HawaSentinelDemo/tools.py)
- Review for any specific tool schema adjustments needed for Gemini (though OpenAI-compatible should work as-is).

